reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars good little vacuum, worth the price
reviews.reviewText: I didn't expect much for this price but didn't want to keep buying canned air dusters. I was pleasantly surprised to find that the suction on this thing is pretty strong. I used it for cleaning the interior of my computer and keyboard and it was very effective. I haven't yet tried the "blower" mode because I don't want to just move the dust into the air. Before buying this unit I was using canned air dusters. The problem with the canned air is that it blows the dust around and you have to keep replacing air cans. This gadget is good because you can recharge it. You can also keep it plugged in (recommended) when using the vacuum feature. It also comes with a nice hand tool for lifting the keys off of your computer keyboard to get underneath.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for maintaining your PC dust-free
reviews.reviewText: After years of dealing with condensed air spray cans and their chemical residues, this seems like a great way to regularly maintain my electronics. My home office is in a tiny room but still manages to collect dust like crazy. My desktop has fans and filters that need to be regularly cleared of dust on top of having my keyboard and workspace also needing maintenance.Thanks to the many accessories provided with this duster, I can easily blow, vacuum, and brush away loose dust and lint. Obviously, you'll want to do this outside - just make sure to unplug all your computer stuff. The duster has a long-lasting battery - I've only charged it fully like twice since I got it. It's a great portable cleaner not just for PC and laptops but also for your car's dashboard. My only issues are that the suction power isn't super powerful so you'll need to make a few passes to pick everything up and also that the smaller attachments can get lost so you'll want to keep them all together in the same box.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars A Decent Vacuum for Multiple Purposes
reviews.reviewText: This is a decent little vacuum that's great for your keyboard as advertised, but it's also good for those little crevices in the seats in your car. I also tried it on the sofa for just some crumb cleanup up and it worked fine. I even tested it on my baseboards. Basically, any place where there might be a little dust or a hard-to-reach place, this is perfect to help clean it up. The suction power is fine. I love the multiple-head attachments though. For the price, it's not a bad little vacuum cleaner.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A Surprisingly Powerful Cleaning Tool for Electronics
reviews.reviewText: When I first ordered the Mini Electronic Cleaner, I wasn't expecting much, but it turned out to be a pleasant surprise. This versatile cleaning tool exceeded my expectations in many ways. Here's why I think it's a valuable addition to any tech-savvy individual's toolkit:Exceptional Performance: 4/5This Mini Electronic Cleaner offers more power than I initially anticipated. As a replacement for canned air, it delivers a powerful stream of air that's perfect for cleaning electronic devices. Dust and debris don't stand a chance, and it's ideal for cleaning not just computers but also car vents, home air conditioner vents, and more. The vacuum function, while not as powerful as traditional vacuums, is still quite effective for small debris and particles. The combination of a blower and vacuum in one device is highly convenient.Attachments for Precision: 5/5The variety of attachments that come with this cleaner make it a versatile tool. Whether you need to clean your keyboard, reach into tight corners, or remove debris from various surfaces, these attachments have got you covered. The inclusion of a keycap remover is a thoughtful touch for keyboard cleaning.User-Friendly and Practical: 4/5The device is relatively straightforward to use, and the attachments are easy to swap out, making it suitable for both tech enthusiasts and beginners. The vacuum and blower functions work effectively, making it a practical solution for keeping your electronic devices dust-free.Quiet Operation: 5/5Compared to some older electronic cleaners, this one operates with significantly less noise. It won't disrupt your environment or annoy those around you while you're cleaning your devices.Overall Verdict: 4.5/5The Mini Electronic Cleaner is a fantastic tool for anyone looking to maintain their electronic devices. It combines the power of a blower and a vacuum in one compact device, making it versatile and convenient. While it may not replace a heavy-duty vacuum for larger cleaning tasks, it excels at precision cleaning, making it perfect for keyboards, computer components, and other small electronic devices. Plus, it's an eco-friendly alternative to canned air, saving you money in the long run. If you're tired of buying cans of compressed air, this electronic cleaner is a worthy investment that will help you keep your devices in top shape.
